Introduced Version
HOUSE BILL No. 1184
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 24-14.
Synopsis: Towing matters. Provides that a towing company that
performs emergency towing or commercial private property towing
shall reimburse the owner of the motor vehicle for any damage caused
by the towing company. Provides that a commercial private property
owner that establishes a tow-away zone must post a tow-away zone
sign at the location of the tow-away zone that is at a reasonable height,
conspicuous, and clearly visible to the public.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Haggard, Morris
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Roads and Transportation.
