2
1 owner that establishes a tow-away zone under this section must post a
2 tow-away zone sign at the location of the tow-away zone that is at a
3 reasonable height, conspicuous, and clearly visible to the public. A
4 tow-away zone sign described under this section shall provide the
5 following information:
6 (1) A statement that the area in the immediate vicinity of the sign
7 is a tow-away zone.
8 (2) Pertinent contact information.
9 (3) A description of any person permitted to park in the affected
10 area, if applicable.
11 (b) A commercial private property owner may have a motor vehicle
12 towed from the owner's commercial private property without first
13 displaying signage concerning the tow-away zone if the motor vehicle
14 is removed under IC 9-22-1-16.
15 (c) A unit (as defined in IC 36-1-2-23) may adopt an ordinance that
16 provides for different requirements than those provided in this section.
